or-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-b6fd8dd elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"b6fd8dd\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5ddee0b\" data-id=\"5ddee0b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7d41412 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"7d41412\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Appearance: How do rabbits look different from other animals?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-38bef23 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"38bef23\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><b>Rabbits<\/b> are often compared to hares and other small furry creatures. However, what sets them apart is their physical appearance. <b>Rabbits<\/b> have long ears that can rotate up to 270 degrees, allowing them to catch sounds from different directions effectively. Their hind legs are also longer than the front ones, making them fast runners capable of escaping predators.<\/p>\n<p>Another notable feature of rabbits is their fur. They have a soft, dense coat that provides insulation against cold temperatures. The coloration of their fur varies from one breed to another but can be predominantly brown or gray with white patches on the belly and tail area. Additionally, rabbits possess sharp claws for digging and powerful teeth for chewing vegetation.<\/p>\n<p>Keep your home clean with our proven ways to control<b>&nbsp;<\/b><a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/norway-rats\/\" target=\"_blank\"><u><b>Norway rats<\/b><\/u><\/a>&nbsp;in your home.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-26602ec elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"26602ec\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Habitat<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-63844ef elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"63844ef\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Rabbits are known to be burrowing animals. They create their habitats by digging up the earth and making a complex system of tunnels that can reach several feet underground. These tunnels are used as sleeping quarters and protect them from predators such as foxes, hawks, and snakes.<\/p><p>Rabbits prefer to live in open fields, meadows, and forests where they can easily find food. The vegetation around their habitats is essential for survival since they feed on leaves, bark, fruits, and plant seeds. They also rely on the grasses around them for cover when they are outside of their burrows.<\/p><p>When building their homes, rabbits use various materials, such as twigs or dried plant stems, to reinforce the walls of their burrows. The entrance is usually small, so it&#8217;s difficult for predators to enter. Additionally, rabbits have multiple entrances leading into the same tunnel system so they can escape through another exit in case one entrance is blocked or compromised.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-081e1c9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"081e1c9\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Behaviour: What are some common behaviours of rabbits?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2866cc8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2866cc8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Rabbits are known for their unique behaviours, making them interesting and fun pets. One of the most common behaviours of rabbits is digging. These <b>animals<\/b> love to dig, whether it&#8217;s in the soil, carpet, or furniture. Providing them with a designated area to dig freely without damaging your property is important.<\/p><p>Another behaviour that is typical of rabbits is binkying. Binkying refers to when rabbits jump and twist in mid-air, often accompanied by flicking their ears or shaking their head. This playful behaviour usually occurs when they are happy and content. It&#8217;s a great sign that your bunny is enjoying life.<\/p><p>Lastly, rabbits also display territorial aggression towards other <b>rabbits<\/b> or even humans if they feel threatened or uncomfortable. They may thump their back legs on the ground as a warning sign or lunge at an intruder with their teeth bared. Understanding these signs is important to avoid provoking your rabbit and maintain a peaceful relationship.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-012de64 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"012de64\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Diet: What kind of food should rabbits eat<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cd6117c elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cd6117c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Rabbits are known to be herbivorous animals that require a high-fibre diet for proper digestion. Their diets primarily comprise hay, vegetables, and limited quantities of fruits. Fresh timothy hay should make up the most significant part of their diet as it helps maintain their dental health while providing them with essential fibre.<\/p><p>In addition to hay, rabbits should also consume leafy greens such as spinach, kale, cilantro, and parsley. However, these greens must be introduced gradually into their diet to prevent digestive issues such as diarrhea or bloating. Vegetables like carrots can also serve as treats for rabbits due to their high sugar content, but they must be given in moderation.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-79a643a elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"79a643a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Reproduction: How do rabbits reproduce and what are their litters?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-efb9926 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"efb9926\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>It is known for its breeding habits, female rabbits are capable of producing more than one litter in a year. Rabbit reproduction is unique from other mammals, with a short gestation period of about 30 days. Female rabbits can breed from the age of four months and continue to produce litters until the age of six years.<\/p><p>The mating process for rabbits is quick, usually lasting no more than a few seconds. Males mount females several times during the mating season until successful mating occurs. A female can produce an average of eight offspring per litter, although some breeds may have larger or smaller litter sizes. Newborn rabbits, also known as kits, are born hairless and blind but grow rapidly in the first few weeks after birth.<\/p><p>The care and development of her litter after birth is left entirely to the mother rabbit. A doe will nurse her young for about four weeks with milk produced in special glands in her abdomen before gradually weaning over time. With proper nutrition and care, baby rabbits will soon grow into independent adults ready to have babies of their own in a few months!<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-44524eb elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"44524eb\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-56cfa7e\" data-id=\"56cfa7e\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-25095e6\" data-id=\"25095e6\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d3b0a14 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d3b0a14\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Humane Wildlife Removal Service<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9c9dded elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9c9dded\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Acme Pest Solutions offers humane wildlife removal services to ensure the safety and well-being of both animals and humans.<\/p><div class=\"flex-1 overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-vlfjz-79elbk h-full dark:bg-gray-800\"><div class=\"react-scroll-to-bottom--css-vlfjz-1n7m0yu\"><div class=\"flex flex-col items-center text-sm dark:bg-gray-800\"><div class=\"group w-full text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 border-b border-black\/10 dark:border-gray-900\/50 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-[#444654]\"><div class=\"text-base gap-4 md:gap-6 md:max-w-2xl lg:max-w-xl xl:max-w-3xl p-4 md:py-6 flex lg:px-0 m-auto\"><div class=\"relative flex w-[calc(100%-50px)] flex-col gap-1 md:gap-3 lg:w-[calc(100%-115px)]\"><div class=\"flex flex-grow flex-col gap-3\"><div class=\"min-h-[20px] flex flex-col items-start gap-4 whitespace-pre-wrap\"><div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light\"><p>Our team at Acme Pest Solutions is trained to handle a variety of wildlife species and uses <strong>eco-friendly and humane<\/strong> methods to ensure the safety of both the animals and the environment.<\/p><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c98e910 elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-global elementor-global-4670 elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"c98e910\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-lg\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/appointment\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Book An Appointment<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-728bbc4\" data-id=\"728bbc4\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-93a29cf elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"93a29cf\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-a0b1cd5\" data-id=\"a0b1cd5\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9a3d315 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"9a3d315\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Health risks: What health problems can rabbit cause, and how serious are they?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ad62932 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ad62932\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Rabbits are generally considered harmless pets, but they can carry a variety of diseases that pose health risks to humans. Symptoms include high fever, headaches, muscle aches, and swollen lymph nodes. Although it&#8217;s rare for people to contract this disease from rabbits, it&#8217;s important to take precautions such as wearing gloves when handling them.<\/p><p>Another health risk associated with rabbits is allergies. People who are allergic to rabbits may experience symptoms such as sneezing, runny nose, and hives when exposed to their fur or dander. In severe cases, asthma attacks can also occur. It&#8217;s recommended that people with rabbit allergies avoid contact with them or take antihistamines before interacting with these animals.<\/p><p>Finally, rabbits can also transmit parasites such as fleas and mites to humans. These parasites can cause itching and skin irritation in both humans and animals alike. To prevent the spread of these pests from rabbits to other pets or humans in the household, regular grooming and flea prevention measures should be implemented for all animals in the home.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5142dec elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"5142dec\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Preventing rabbit invasions: Tips for keeping your property free from these pests<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-af7d84a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"af7d84a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Rabbits may look cute and harmless, but they can cause serious damage to gardens and crops. Preventing rabbit invasions is essential for keeping your property free from these pests. One of the most effective ways to discourage rabbits from entering your property is by using a physical barrier such as a fence. The fence should be at least two feet high, with mesh openings no larger than one inch in diameter.<\/p><p>Another way to keep rabbits away from your property is by eliminating their food source. This means removing any vegetables, fruits, or other plants that attract them. You can also use repellents such as predator urine or spicy sprays around the perimeter of your garden to deter rabbits from coming near.<\/p><p>Finally, trapping and relocating rabbits may be necessary if their presence persists despite preventative measures. It&#8217;s important to note that wild rabbits can carry diseases so handling them with care or seeking professional assistance from ACME Pest Solutions when dealing with rabbit invasions on your property is crucial.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Rabbits Identification Color Size Description Color Rabbits come in various colours, ranging from white to black, brown, grey or even mixed patterns. Size Rabbits can reach up to 80 cm in length. Description Rabbits front legs are shorter than their hind legs, which allows them to move quickly and jump high. Rabbits also have strong &#8230; <a title=\"Rabbits\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/rabbits\/\" aria-label=\"More on Rabbits\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6651,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[37],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6504","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-pest-libraries"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6504"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=6504"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6504\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/6651"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=6504"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=6504"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=6504"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}